1. use .env file to store all environment related variables
2. use Auth0 for basic authentication
3. store user info to flask g context so that we can use it anywhere without the need to pass it in Authorization header
4. use git pre commit hooks to scan all the files to be committed for syntax check using flake8, beautified using black, organize import statements using isort and many more
5. for logging use sentry its one of the best service for logging exceptions and log data it reduces the pain of findind what went wron and where saving thousand of hours for a developer and makes development much faster
